HEADWORD: Harmonically
<hw>Har*mon"ic*al*ly</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an harmonical manner;
harmoniously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In respect to harmony, as distinguished from
<xex>melody</xex>; <as>as, a passage <ex>harmonically</ex>
correct</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>In harmonical
progression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmonicon</ent>⟦br⟧
